<!-- COMMS PROTOCOL — READ FIRST -->

This repo can use `comms` (github.com/dpa-plus/comms) for opt-in multi-agent coordination.

Only start the workflow when the user explicitly asks to use `comms` or invokes the `using-comms` skill.

**When the workflow starts:**
```bash
COMMS_ACTOR=codex-20260527-a comms hello
COMMS_ACTOR=codex-20260527-a comms status
```
Pick one concrete per-session actor and reuse it for this conversation.

If cwd discovery fails with `operation not permitted`, run from a safe cwd and
target the repo explicitly:
```bash
cd /tmp
COMMS_ACTOR=codex-20260527-a comms --repo /absolute/repo/path status
```

**UI / session archive:**
The user may open `comms ui` to watch the workflow. The UI can start/end the
whole project-level comms session and exposes backend metadata at
`GET /api/status`: `actions`, `current_session.events`, and
`comms_sessions[].events`. Agents should still coordinate through the CLI unless
the user explicitly asks them to inspect the UI API.

**Before any file edit during the workflow:**
```bash
COMMS_ACTOR=codex-20260527-a comms claim "src/path/to/file.ts" --intent "what you're changing"
```
If exit code 1: read stderr, surface the conflict to the user, ask whether the prior session is alive. If user authorizes, use `--steal <id> --reason "..."`.

**When done with a claim:**
```bash
COMMS_ACTOR=codex-20260527-a comms release --result "PR #123 merged"
```

**Record findings:**
```bash
COMMS_ACTOR=codex-20260527-a comms find fix "..." --ref path:src/foo.ts --ref commit:abc1234
COMMS_ACTOR=codex-20260527-a comms find bug "..." --ref path:src/bar.ts
COMMS_ACTOR=codex-20260527-a comms find decision "..." --ref doc:slug
COMMS_ACTOR=codex-20260527-a comms find gotcha "..." --ref path:src/auth.ts
COMMS_ACTOR=codex-20260527-a comms find ship "..." --ref pr:#123
```

**Global lessons:**
Use `comms lesson --list` and `comms lesson <slug>` for curated cross-project
agent lessons. Do not add a lesson unless the user explicitly asks or approves
the proposed lesson.

Do not install hooks or edit shell startup files unless the user explicitly asks.

